The paper proposes a novel graph-driven generative model for heterogeneous multi-task learning, which involves combining a graph convolutional network (GCN) with multiple variational autoencoders. The focus of the paper is on healthcare applications, including clinical topic modeling, procedure recommendation, and admission-type prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves image processing (using GCN), which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with healthcare data, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
